article.description: Matt Freije scored 32 points and went 13-for-15 from the free throw line to help Vanderbilt hold off an Alabama comeback and win 70-67 Wednesday.
article.headline: Freije's 32 help stave off Tide rally
article.linkText: Vandy edges Bama to help NCAA cause
article.story: TUSCALOOSA, Ala. (AP) -- Matt Freije scored 32 points and went 13-for-15 from the free throw line to help Vanderbilt hold off an Alabama comeback and win 70-67 Wednesday. Freije helped Vanderbilt (16-6, 5-6 Southeastern Conference) dominate the first half, accounting for 21 of the Commodores' first 27 points. Alabama (12-10, 4-7) trailed by 21 points in the first half but fought back in the second to tie the game 60-60 with 4:33 to play. Chuck Davis evened the score with a dunk, but Vanderbilt scored the next six points on two free throws by Scott Hundley, a basket by Corey Smith and another two from Freije. Vanderbilt ended the half up 42-24 with a 28-4 run, but the Crimson Tide responded with 14 unanswered points early in the second half to cut the lead to six on a 3-pointer by Davis. Dawid Przybyszewski and Corey Smith each had 10 points for the Commodores. Kennedy Winston had 17, Davis had 16, Earnest Shelton had 15 and Emmett Thomas added 11 for the Crimson Tide. Thomas sank three of four 3-point attempts.
